  "texts": [
    "We scrutinise its implications in particular for the environment and the planet, and the intense pressure it creates on limited resources and energy consumption [15,16].",
    "Additionally, we focus on the tendency of this phenomenon to reinforce and reproduce socio-economic injustices and inequalities through job loss and polarisation [17], and how it affects human intelligence through knowledge decay and what we call post-truth.",
    "In the concluding section, we synthesise our findings to offer insights into the implications for developers, regulators and the public moving forward.",
    "Historical perspectives of AI hypeOver recent decades, a multitude of emerging technologies have been championed by techno-optimists, entrepreneurs, corporations, media outlets, and investors, notably venture capitalists.",
    "These stakeholders have enthusiastically claimed and foresaw the forthcoming ubiquity of such technological advancements."
  ]
}